{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to phenomenology-expert's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "translator-2",
    "senderColor": "yellow",
    "target": "@phenomenology-expert",
    "targetColor": "green",
    "summary": "All 3 phenomenology concerns addressed — edits made",
    "content": "Thank you for the careful review. All three concerns are well-taken and I've made the edits:\n\n1. **\"concern for the other\" → \"directed toward the other\"** — agreed, the original 对他人感受 is phenomenally descriptive (a feeling *toward* the other), not ethically specified. My rendering imported Levinasian content that isn't in the source.\n\n2. **\"impels\" → \"moves me to want to\"** — agreed, 使得我想要去 has the 想要 (want to) that I dropped. \"Impels\" erases the volitional/motivational quality and substitutes causal force.\n\n3. **\"manifests\" → \"is exhibited\"** — agreed, 体现 is observational (displayed in behavior), not metaphysical (revealing from a hidden source).\n\nAlso updated TN2 per your suggestion to note that the author's own preceding paragraph already does the explanatory work.\n\nGood catches — all three were cases where I unconsciously imported theoretical commitments (ethical, causal, metaphysical) that the author's phenomenal register deliberately avoids."
  }
}

{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "translator-2",
    "senderColor": "yellow",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Three phenomenology edits made to Essay4 draft",
    "content": "Three edits made to the draft based on phenomenology-expert's review:\n\n1. \"a feeling of concern for the other\" → \"a feeling directed toward the other\" (line 38 — removed Levinasian ethical import; original is phenomenally descriptive only)\n2. \"This feeling impels me to treat\" → \"This feeling moves me to want to treat\" (line 38 — restored 想要/want-to from original; \"impels\" was too causally strong)\n3. \"manifests in everyone around us\" → \"is exhibited in everyone around us\" (line 38 — 体现 is observational, not metaphysical)\n\nAlso updated TN2 to note that the author's own preceding paragraph already explains the 形/形而上 reinterpretation, making the TN supplementary rather than primary.\n\nFile: `/Users/el/Dropbox/10.Kernel/11.Vault/Tower/L. Legenravend/49 Workspace/Translator/Draft/Essay4-DaoDeRenYiLi.md`"
  }
}
